t_type":"person","locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-11-06T00:11:38Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Justin Tomlinson","withdrawn":false,"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/justin-tomlinson","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/justin-tomlinson"},{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/amber-rudd","base_path":"/government/people/amber-rudd","content_id":"85395ec8-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","document_type":"person","locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-11-06T00:11:09Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Amber Rudd","withdrawn":false,"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/amber-rudd","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/amber-rudd"}],"primary_publishing_organisation":[{"analytics_identifier":"D10","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions","base_path":"/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions","content_id":"b548a09f-8b35-4104-89f4-f1a40bf3136d","document_type":"organisation","locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Department for Work and Pensions","withdrawn":false,"details":{"logo":{"formatted_title":"Department<br/>for Work &amp; <br/>Pensions","crest":"single-identity"},"brand":"department-for-work-pensions","default_news_image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/35/s300_dwp-caxton-house-logo-960.jpg","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/35/s960_dwp-caxton-house-logo-960.jpg"}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions"}],"roles":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--48","base_path":"/government/ministers/minister-of-state--48","content_id":"7ed9acaf-cd72-49c6-8773-de94b753ef0c","document_type":"ministerial_role","locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-08-12T13:31:37Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Minister of State (Minister for Disabled People, Health and Work)","withdrawn":false,"details":{"body":"<p>The minister’s responsibilities include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>responsible for the departmental strategy on disability and disability employment</li>\n  <li>cross-government responsibility for disabled people</li>\n  <li>Employment and Support Allowance, Personal Independence Payment, Disability Living Allowance and elements of Universal Credit that relate to disabled people including the Severe Disability Premium</li>\n  <li>EU exit oversight including citizens’ rights and no deal preparation</li>\n  <li>work and health strategy including sponsorship of the joint Department for Work and Pensions and Department of Health and Social Care Work and Health Unit</li>\n  <li>disability benefit reform</li>\n  <li>devolution framework</li>\n  <li>Carer’s Allowance</li>\n  <li>motability and arms-length compensation schemes</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"call-to-action\">\n<p>The role of Minister of State for Disabled People, Health and Work replaced the role of <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state-minister-for-disabled-people\">Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Disabled People</a> in July 2016.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--48","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/minister-of-state--48"},{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions","base_path":"/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions","content_id":"845e6272-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","document_type":"ministerial_role","locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2018-01-10T10:52:23Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Secretary of State for Work and Pensions","withdrawn":false,"details":{"body":"<p>The Secretary of State has overall responsibility for the Department for Work and Pensions (<abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr>). They have direct responsibility for departmental expenditure and departmental management.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> is responsible for the administration of the State Pension and working age benefits system, providing support to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>people of working age</li>\n  <li>employers</li>\n  <li>pensioners</li>\n  <li>families and children</li>\n  <li>disabled people</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions"}],"available_translations":[{"title":"Thousands of pensioners to benefit from PIP assessment overhaul","public_updated_at":"2019-07-09T08:30:05Z","document_type":"press_release","schema_name":"news_article","base_path":"/government/news/thousands-of-pensioners-to-benefit-from-pip-assessment-overhaul","api_path":"/api/content/government/news/thousands-of-pensioners-to-benefit-from-pip-assessment-overhaul","withdrawn":false,"content_id":"05b616d8-aa0f-4dc5-80c1-46cad0e18c40","locale":"en","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/news/thousands-of-pensioners-to-benefit-from-pip-assessment-overhaul","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/thousands-of-pensioners-to-benefit-from-pip-assessment-overhaul","links":{}}]},"description":"Unnecessary reassessments for Personal Independence Payments (PIP) are today (9 July 2019) being scrapped for around 290,000 disabled pensioners.","details":{"body":"<p>Work and Pensions Secretary Amber Rudd first announced in March that people receiving <abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr> who have reached State Pension age will no longer have their awards regularly reviewed, instead moving to a light touch review at 10 years.</p>\n\n<p>Work and Pensions Secretary Amber Rudd said:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>I want the benefit system to be a source of support for disabled people, not a source of worry. That’s why we’re scrapping needless <abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr> reassessments for pensioners whose situation is unlikely to change.</p>\n\n  <p class=\"last-child\">This underlines our commitment to ensuring that the most vulnerable get the support they’re entitled to.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Light touch reviews will mean pensioners will not be asked to attend a face-to-face assessment unless their needs have changed.</p>\n\n<p>Minister for Disabled People Justin Tomlinson said:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>I want to ensure we live in a fair and decent society in which all of us, whatever age or ability, have an equal chance to live a fulfilling life.</p>\n\n  <p class=\"last-child\">We are committed to ensuring that everyone receives the support they’re entitled to, allowing them to live independently.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Last month this improvement was applied to all new <abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr> claimants who reached State Pension age before their planned re-assessment. From today it will start being applied to existing <abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr> claimants over State Pension age.</p>\n\n<p>The changes will benefit pensioners whose personal circumstances are unlikely to change.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr> was introduced in 2013 to replace the outdated Disability Living Allowance (<abbr title=\"Disability Living Allowance\">DLA</abbr>) system. <abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr> is a fairer benefit, which assesses the way an individual’s health condition or disability impacts them while completing daily activities, such as cooking or taking a shower.</p>\n\n<p>Other recent improvements to <abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr> include trialling the video recording of assessments to improve transparency and build trust in the process.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"contact-press-office\">Contact Press Office</h2>\n\n<p>Media enquiries for this press release – 020 3267 5106</p>\n\n<div id=\"contact_df0a78d2-6122-46ac-8014-6f8c5e0b8d3f\" class=\"contact postal-address\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Press Office</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n      <p class=\"adr\">\n<span class=\"street-address\">Caxton House\n<br>\nTothill Street</span><br>\n<span class=\"locality\">London</span><br>\n<span class=\"postal-code\">SW1H 9NA</span>\n</p>\n\n    \n    \n      <div class=\"email-url-number\">\n      \n      \n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">London Press Office (national media and London area enquiries only – not questions about personal claims)</span>\n          020 3267 5144\n        </p>\n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Out-of-hours (journalists only)</span>\n          07623 928 975\n        </p>\n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">England and Wales (local media enquiries)</span>\n          029 20 586 then 097 or 098 or 099\n        </p>\n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Scotland (local media enquiries)</span>\n          0131 310 1122\n        </p>\n      \n      </div>\n    \n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p>Follow DWP on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.twitter.com/dwppressoffice\">Twitter</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/dwp\">Facebook</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/dwp\">LinkedIn</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/dwp\">YouTube</a></p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n","change_history":[{"note"